Marcius Rex: as proconsul of Cilicia, nc. 67, he had been of very little assistance to Lucullus in the Mithri- datio War. In 66, in accordance with the terms of the Manilian law, he was superseded by Pompey, at the time when the command of the army of Lucullus was transferred to Pompey. This, however, did not prevent Marcius from claiming a triumph on his return to Italy. Q.
